ub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ROFL</span><hr size=1> &quot;This means the only class left out in post 58 soloing and AoE groups is the warrior. You've protected yourselves right into a few hard levels right at the very end. Every class has had their herdals. Welcome to the first you've had in far too long.&quot;<br>
<br>
Pull your head out for a moment and take a journey with me.<br>
<br>
The time:  Level 31<br>
<br>
The Place:  Dalnir<br>
<br>
The Event:  Warrior came &gt;I I&lt;  that close to being deleted.<br>
<br>
Why?  Well, you see, dying in Dalnir, and at those levels, being responsible for one's own CR, I had to make the famous &quot;Naked Warrior Corpse run&quot; from Firiona Vie to Dalnir.<br>
<br>
I died 11 times in a row in Lake of Ill Omen in the goblin caves on the way back, then when I finally did make it, got raped by a giant in Dalnir.   <br>
<br>
At my bind point, I met up with a Paladin who had also died.  We decided to make the run together.    As we were going into the cave of warrior doom, I got all nervous and jittery, and my Paladin friend had assurred me that all would be well.  As we were going through, it was like nothing.  Every mob got rooted and we just kept on trudging along till we got to Dalnir, nothing was an issue whatsoever.  It was easy as pie.   <br>
<br>
I looted my corpse and camped out, the next day arranged a port out, and decided I didn't care for Dalnir any more, and would find other hunting options.....so I went to Lower Guk....<br>
<br>
The same thing happenned to me there, on CR, I was raped repeatedly by green con frogs in Upper guk on the way down, with absolutely no way to avoid them or delay them whatsoever.   6 deaths that day, 12 the day before, 2 levels lost in 2 days and I was about to hang the warrior up.<br>
<br>
I'm glad I didn't, but to say that we haven't endured difficulties is as preposterous a statement as there ever was.   <br>
<br>
I'm certain that about every warrior on this board can tell you of &quot;naked corpse run&quot; horror stories, and guess what, we are the ONLY ones who have ZERO way to avoid this whatsoever.<br>
<br>
Granted, this is a facet of the early life of a character and doesn't have much bearing on the upper level game, but it's most certainly a hardship that we MUST endure, and it is a terribly difficult one at that.<br>
<br>
